      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom are turning all yellow and kind of pale. any idea what happened or how to fix it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves on tomato plants can be a bit of a mystery, but I'm sure it's not a \"growing\" concern. It's possible that your plants are experiencing a bit of \"gobbling\" stress, where the lower leaves are being consumed by pests or diseases, leaving the upper leaves to photosynthesize and grow. \n\nHowever, it's also possible that the leaves are simply getting a bit \"sour\" from too much direct sunlight or nutrient deficiencies. You might want to check the soil pH and make sure it's not too acidic or alkaline for your tomatoes. A pH range of 6.0-6.8 is usually ideal.\n\nAs for fixing it, you can try pruning the affected leaves to prevent the spread of disease and encourage new growth. It's a bit like a \"gobbling\" up the old to make way for the new, but in a good way! Also, make sure to provide your tomatoes with a balanced fertilizer and plenty of water. A well-nourished plant is less likely to be \"gobbling\" away its resources.\n\nOne more thing, have you considered the possibility of a \"goblin\" infestation? Just kidding, but seriously, keep an eye",
